76561198039745828,Recommended,294100,24835236,"Posted: 11 August, 2016",all,Oktakon,"Rimworld is a young and beautifully seductive... yet cruel and exotic mistress with a severe case of “BPD” (Borderline Personality Disorder) that you’ll find yourself running back to night, after night, after night. Once you understand her language, her …ways, endure her pain and suffering inflicted upon you nightly, and start to survive her fiery and destructive emotional outbursts. You’ll start to see the heavens part and the Godrays pour in on the potential that you can have, sharing a life together in a blissful new world harmony.However, if you mishandle her, miscalculate or neglect her needs, or… even say just one wrong word to her… expect everything you have painstakingly endured and built to be torn down in front of your very own eyes in a blaze of uncontrollable psychotic glory. When that moment finally happens, when the realisation that this thing, this… monster, that you once held so close and dear in your arms with all your hopes and dreams invested into, finally breaks free from its mental restraints of care, stability and love… You find yourself dazed and confused … staring into an endless moment of emotionless hindsight.You face your final moments alive on whatever world you have tried to stake out a living on in silence… you watch as your cooks arms are blown off by raiders that have stolen some new GlitterTech incendiary weaponry that is now setting your whole map, base, settlers and outer defences on fire… but its ok you never liked his simple cooked one ingredient meals that gave you food poisoning anyway……. WATCH IN HORROR!!!….. as your newly hatched chickens are beaten to death in melee and your pet house cat “Snuggles” neck is cut in cold blood, just because one of your own settlers is in a psychotic mood that their room isn’t as beautiful as someone’s else’s….. sigh R.I.P Snuggles and baby chicken nuggets.And finally watch as your last settler alive succumbs to extreme heatstroke that your whole base was suffering from, and dies on the floor of his very own room, his last thoughts of wishing that he had laid better quality floor boards… but just never had the time to do it…as his vison fades to darkness…Because, you see, an eclipse has blocked the sun for last 2 days which has knocked out your solar panel farm and drained the backup batteries that was once powering all of your bases air conditioners. Just then a solar flare event takes place that wipes out all electrically powered devices, so those wood fuel generators that you just built over the last 2 days to compensate for the loss of power the eclipse caused… are now useless.Then the left hook comes out of nowhere, that one you did not see coming, oh yes… an epic heatwave just shows up to say “hey, how you doin” …. pushing your global temps to 55+ degrees Celsius even in the shade. Without cooling available it effectively and slowly turns all living things into a sack of sizzling seductive bacon…. Hmmm bacon.In the famous words of Private Hicks “Game over man .. Game over!.“9.5/10 - Current Alpha StateConsidering that this is still an alpha stage game, RimWorld shows a remarkable amount of polish and potential, however, whenever you do find a shortcoming with a game mechanic you don’t quite like, I guarantee you there’s a mod to meld this game into your style of play or aesthetic pleasure.The modding community on steam and the official forums is also very strong with new mods, updates and tweaks being added almost daily at the time of this review.A big plus for me also is that the developer listens to the modding community, and has quite simply stated that there are certain things he wants to expand in the final game content. And has announced to the modding community to focus creating those elements for it to be implemented into possible future alpha builds.As a student game developer I love this idea and will implement into my own game development plan when that time happens.Also for those that haven’t clocked like 50+ hrs on similar games like “Prison Architect” you will initially struggle. I’m not going to lie there’s currently a very steep learning curve even with the adaptive tutor enabled, but once you get over it, it’s pretty simple and has very enjoyable concepts to understand and master.These are all my reasons I have given RimWorld a Terminator 2 sinking fiery thumbs up."
