,Recommended,294100,33447053,Posted: 10 July,all,Nick,"Incredible game.Rimworld has tremendous depth as a colony management simulation, You are in charge of your colonist's needs and keeping them happy and healthy is no mean feat.They will break, physically, you have to deal with raider incursions, whether it's 6 pirates with M4s attempting to pillage and kidnap your colonists, or raids of 30+ tribe members equipped with basic weapons trying to burn down your base.Mechanoids with devastating weapons arrive in their drop pods and crashed ships ready to incinerate you and sharp-clawed insectoids which spawn at the most inopportune times possible will attempt to decapitate your colonists.It's not just physical threats though, mental breaks are common on the Rim, whether because a colonist lost a family member in a raid, or because your ""Abrasive"" colonist insulted them at breakfast, social fights, berserker rages and depressed wandering (often in inclement weather) are all possible.To defend from the threats you have to build a secure base, it has to be fireproof, of course, lightning strikes are just one of the ways it can end in a blaze of glory.Your food will rot if you don't refrigerate it, making that elephant hunt you just wasted a colonist on less fruitful until you have a freezer room. Equally, frostbite is a threat in the Winter months, so you must craft warm clothes, even swaggy clothes like the bowler and cowboy hats to keep the colonists warm.Your colonists will have a set of traits which determine their ability or inability to perform certain actions such as hauling, mining, doctoring and crafting to name but a few of the systems. They will sometimes be passionate about these tasks, learning them more quickly than anyone else, but other traits can make them quick to mentally break if you task them to dangerous work in ugly environments.There are a hundred tricks you have to learn to survive in Rimworld, and you will learn more each time the AI storyteller you chose destroys you. And they will destroy you, Cassandra on a slow but ramping curve, Phoebe with big raids between breathers and Randy with multiple raids or diseases or toxic fallouts at once.It's not all gloom though, although every action you take to increase the survivability of your colony will make future raids against you stronger, you can use some of the wealth you generate to form makeshift alliances with other nearby Factions and call them in, to sell you more slaves  or weapons, or to assist in fighting your battles.The latest update (which are very frequent, despite this game being polished as hell already) made it possible to traverse the world in a caravan and collect treasures from around the world, providing you have enough food and weapons to make it there and back alive with the booty!There is a big modding community with many quality-of-life fixes for the game, as well as system improvements and even star wars and cthulu mods.But the vanilla game itself is exceptional and sells itself, I don't write reviews and Rimworld made me write this, it's that good.If you like trying to spin 10 plates at once and getting wrecked when you take your eye off of too many at once, buy it. This game is brutal, this game is frustrating but above all this game is fun."
76561197971724802,Recommended,294100,32104942,Posted: 1 June,all,Pontifex Maximus,"InRimWorld, it’s your job to manage the lives of crash-landed survivors, with the ultimate goal of living long enough to construct a shuttle in order to escape the hostile planet you’ve landed on.In order to do so, first, you’ll have to construct a base capable of withstanding the AI’s ever-increasing threats. Half of the fun is in designing your base however you want to, just make sure it has some sturdy defenses since the game’s surprisingly complex combat system takes such things as cover, concealment, and range into consideration.Your characters are randomly generated and have their own advantages, disadvantages, and even relations to one another in some cases. You also choose what type of environment you want to begin in: jungle, arctic, desert, and several other biomes. You must be aware that the more extreme climates are much more of a challenge to settle within. Although you will get raided from time to time, or perhaps attacked by some random animals, much of the fun to be had inRimWorldis just seeing how your colonists interact with each other, as well as how they deal with different situations.RimWorldis a fantastic survival simulation game and although it is still in Early Access, it already has a wealth of content to indulge in.It's an exciting new game that offers a highly unique take on the ever-growing survival genre. It combines colorful, detailed graphics, along with engaging game mechanics. Each game is very different from others and unfolds organically, allowing for virtually limitless replay value.If you’re even remotely interested in survival games, or games in which you actually begin to care about your little digital protagonists, then grab a copy ofRimWorld.THE GOOD- One of the best simulations in recent memory- Detailed graphics- Great game mechanics- A story of your own creativityTHE BAD- Still Early Access10/10DISASTER | BAD | MEDIOCRE | OKAY | GOOD | GREAT | AMAZING |MASTERPIECE"
