76561197960694364,Recommended,294100,26284287,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,Arctic Monkey,"Imagine this: take some of the crisis management of FTL and mix it with some open-world resource-gathering survival aspects of Don't Starve.  Add a research tech tree, enough tools to stretch your creativity with time/resource/task management a little bit similar to Prison Architect, and throw in some hilarious and often tense character interactions.  Make the game easy enough to build mods for that the community runs wild and adds tons of fantastic content.  Then try something totally crazy and have the *story itself* be procedurally generated.  This doesn't sound like a great combination ot ideas to put into a single game, but it works so well it blows me away.  Everyone likes to share the stories they experienced, and below is my favorite.I created the entire crew of Firefly complete with quirks and relationships, then over a few years of game time had them carefully carve out a massive cave in the side of a mountain in the shape of the Serenity ship hull, acurrate in scale and layout to the ""real"" thing.  I was overjoyed when Mal and Inara hit it off right away and eventually got married, and Kaylee eventually found some romance with a wandering native she helped rescue.  They were really unhappy for a while until the crew quarters were finished with double-beds so they could finalle snuggle together at night.  It was a challenge protecting all the livestock from bandits and keeping the forest from burning during those dry thunderstorms.  But in the end, I love my crew.Here are a few of the notes from that game (mostly how Simon is terrible):-Day 4: Jon wanders into camp and joins up, looking for big game.  Over the years he gets his fill while fighting some maneater muffalo and lost his hand, and later while fighting a mad pack of rhinos he lost his nose and left leg, and his left eye later on defending against some raiders.  Poor guy.-Day 17: Jon broke and threw a tantrum because he was cold, because he slept in the freezer, like an idiot-Day 41: The god****ed rabbits are multiplying so fast they are eating all the grass and starving themselves, so we're butchering all that are starving, that'll teach 'em-Day 66: Simon, when rebuffed by Inara, went on a rage streak.  He didn't cause much damage because he's so weak. But he lost his right pinky when he picked a fight with one of my huskies.  Mal came to knock his a** out.-Day 67: Simon showing signs of cracking mostly because he's been turned down by Kaylee and Inara (who is married, what a jerk).  Yep, Simon is a little child and broke because of hideous environment.  He started attacking River, who just recovered from her own mental break and was still naked.  Janye knocked his a** out.-Day 68: Simon, being the bbaby that he is, goes berserk and attacks a husky again.  Zoe has none of his crap, disrespecing Mal's party, and punches him to the floor.  He can heal in bed during the party.-Day 72: Middle of the night some bugs spawned and wrecked the crew.  Booke lost a leg, everyone lost some blood.  Simon, once again, went berserk because he's a stupid child and couldn't handle it.  I hate that guy.-Day 101: Overnight a dry thunderstorm threatened to burn our fodder and livestock, tried putting it out.  Simon is a tard.  He keeps catching on fire while trying to put it out.  He is so damn useless.-Day 131: The crew discovers they can capture bandits and harvest organs from the prisoner to transplant into the crew (mostly Jon) to repair battle damage.-Day 135: We are no longer worried about harvesting organs.  So Wash threw a party.  Too bad we're going to harvest some more.-Day 139: Captured a new victim to harvest organs from, muwahaha.-Day 200'ish: The Serenity cave is finished.  There was a new alpha relesase that broke my save game unfortunately, and that was the end of that story."
