,Recommended,294100,25220364,"Posted: 28 August, 2016",all,Dingo,"Rimworld is a very good game on its own, but is still being actively developed with additional content. Mods for this game are highly mature and expand the base game even more, making it a truly diverse and enjoyable simulation of running a colony.If you have fond memories of the early days of Minecraft and Terraria, enjoy games like Prison Architect or Cities: Skylines and want a game that tries to blend everything together, look no further. It might seem overwhelming but it really isn't hard to pick up and play right off the bat."
76561198015456313,Recommended,294100,25405649,"Posted: 7 September, 2016",all,hellbiter88,"I found this game had a steep learning curve. Thankfully the latest alpha release includes a tutorial and sort of an in-game ""wiki"" for different items. The game itself is beyond fantastic. This game is early access but honestly plays better than most stable live releases. Once you understand the game, you can customize virtually every aspect of your colony by setting gamerules--and the rich modding community allows for some truly epic possibilities.As for the gameplay itself, it functions as a 2D survival/base-builder game. You select a group of colonists who crashland on a ""rimworld"", a sort-of ""backwater planet"" on the edges of space. Your goal is to build a self-sustaining colony and ultimately construct another ship to leave the planet (although you can easily just sandbox this game and you really never have to leave). There are multiple difficulty settings, and there are even built-in debug tools if you enjoy cheating/pure sandboxing it.Gameplay includes building, hunting, combat, agriculture, production lines/crafting, trade, and even medicine. The latter is a particularly interesting aspect because not only can you treat injuries, you can perform surgeries on your colonists such as organ transplants, bionic upgrades--and you can even harvest prisoner's organs and sell them on the black market. Newest update lets you grow, manufacture and sell drugs, as well, if that's your type of thing.There really is no limit to this game. It's a complete time-sink and one of the most entertaining EA games I've ever owned."
,Recommended,294100,24539134,"Posted: 26 July, 2016",all,Sliced Ham 2012 (🤠 Ride 'Em),"In the almost 4 days I have owned this game, I've gotten so many stories out of failure or success. Rimworld is truly a good game. Now, I know it may sound copy-pasted that I mention Dwarf Fortress, but Rimworld never fails to make me miss the days of old when I played DF day and night. There are tons of things to do in Rimworld despite the fact it's in alpha, which took me by surprise honestly. I'm gonna chop my review up in to 3 parts to give you a better understanding of the game.You heard this is like Dwarf FortressIf you came here thinking either this would be like DF or something close, you aren't wrong. Rimworld seems to always generate stories comparable to it. This game is nowhere near as complex without mods, however. The lack of enemy types and events in comparison is also a bit bad, but to be fair Rimworld is in alpha and has consistent updates. The fights are more about player knowledge of the combat system; in DF it's more about stats than anything. In Rimworld the cover system plays a huge part in whether you win fights. Finally, Rimworld makes you reallyfeelfor your people and animals. That is due in large part to the fact that you tend to be limited to smaller numbers of both than in Dwarf Fortress. In all honesty DF is still much mroe complex and better than this game in many many ways, but Rimworld is truly something special and only serves to prove that these kind of games are simply amazing.Pros and ConsPros-Makes awesome stories-Mods are amazing and add very much to the game, with some even being incorporated into the game itself-Great dev-Very good controls-Can actually challenge you some times no matter how good you are-Tactical gunfights-Pretty meaty amount of stuff to doCons-Usually on the smaller side of max colonists you can have-Pretty steep learning curve, though I personally loved that-The mood system still needs work (ie A miner decides the mine looks ugly since it's made of stone and kills himself)-The raids can be massive with sometimes triple the number of people you haveA Tale of Love and RevengeThis review wouldn't be complete without a little story of my own from my most recent and best colony. This is the story of Seraph and his wife Whitney.They had both survived since the crash with minimal issue, other than Seraph's missing left index finger and Whitney's now mechanical arm, of course. It had been nearly 3 years since they built the first rooms, and all was well. Then one day Inga, our main negotiator, answers the comm to find out a space marine was being chased by tribals and needed help. I thought ""Hey, a good shot would be great for that minigun I have."" and decided to bare the assault of low tech savages. What I wasn't ready for was themassiveammount of them. With all my colonists AND the marine I only had 9 people, while they were attacking with almost 30. With our 5 cougars and 3 timber wolves as a reinforcement team in the event our technology proved not enough, I figured we would win with no trouble at all. Then Seraph lost his arm to a great bow and just kinda snapped. He went in with his trusty uranium longsword and hacked down as many as 4 of the damned locals before getting his skull bashed in. Whitney had been on the other side of the base and had just come through the door to see her husband get his brains splattered all over the defensive area. She was always something special in combat, wearing power armor and a shield in addition to a bionic arm with retactable claws; she was a melee godess using her masterwork steel gladius. I sent her out as I had no other melee users left and most of my shooters were down or running away. She charged forth with, what I imagine, anger and hate burning in her heart. She butchered all the remaining Tribespeople, sending arms flying, heads rolling, eyes to the ground, and bringing internal organs to the light of day. She had lost her right eye in the fight, the result of a spearman's attack on her. I may have lost my best hunter that day, but I gained the most badass warrior of all time.Overall I give Rimworld a solid 9/10 and would highly recommend it to anyone who likes these type of games."
