,Not Recommended,294100,33760228,Posted: 24 July,all,Tha Pink Guy,"Rimworld is a fantastic game and has so much potential but because of an early design decision by the devs I cannot recommend this game. Rimworld is single threaded which means ultimately it has a hard cap on what it can do before it grinds to a halt.You can easily get 30 hours out of a colony but the game will start slowing down immensly. Now if you keep everything small and hard cap yourself to 1-10 survivors and regularly optimize the game manually or have a mod that does it for you then this game would be fun.I have a lot of respect for the devs especially Tynan. I understand that it would take a lot of work and would have to change rimworld at it's core which Tynan has said he is just not willing to commit to.This thread pretty much sums it up:https://ludeon.com/forums/index.php?topic=17357.0To quote Vas:""How exactly do you come to this conclusion?  Lets say you have a 4 core machine at 3.6GHz like mine.Single Core/Thread: Game starts to lag behind because you have a massive base, it's too much data for one core to handle.  Everything gets queued up to run in proper logical order of events.  Game slows down to handle that slowdown in processing queue.MultiCore/Thread: Game is able to offload some work to different threads.  Thread 1 handles temperature changes.  Thread 2 handles pawn hauling jobs.  Thread 3 handles Pawn Cleaning jobs including snow and calculates whee they should go next each job.  Thread 4 handles pawn hunger and tiredness levels, beauty calculations and other such.  Thread 5 handles mental levels and thought defs.  Thread 6 handles power grid states.  Thread 7 handles random event calculations.  Thread 8 handles Animals and Plants on the map.  Game runs at normal/fast speeds because there is nothing waiting in line to be executed.And don't give me that ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ about buying a single core 10GHz CPU in order to play games.  No.  Unacceptable.  This game is one of those that has too much data for a single core to process."""
