,Recommended,294100,24994455,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,Fidelfc,"I was reluctant to buy this game, being an Early Access game with simple graphics and a hefty price, but i'm so glad i changed my mind.Trying to explain what the game is really hard, due to all mechanics it have, so i'll focus on what i would want to know:This game is what I've been wanting to play my whole life and didn't knew, this is the beautiful son of Dwarf Fortress and The sims, in a very awesome way.The mechanics are deep,but not drag the game down, the learning curve is sometimes brutal, but lovely, the colonist have a lot of ""personality"" and the most memorable stories are created by how faulty they are, as i said, think of dwarf fortress but focusing more in your dworfs as single beings.Also, while this is an Early access game,this development is more like a Don't Starve EA, the updates are very ""feature complete"", you won't get a bunch of features that don't work or need a lot of balancing, you get one or two per version, but they are solid, tested and pretty much bug free, with a  few hotfixes solving the problems, this make the game looks like a complete game that is always evolving.The updates come in a steady way, 2 or 3 months per big update.The modding community is healthy and very active, the developer is very present in both the official forums and in the Reddit subreddit, implementing some suggestions and ignoring the ones that didn't fit the game."
