76561198004311298,Recommended,294100,25001111,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,Miradus,"Rimworld. Kept hearing about this game from my friends but wasn't sure it was for me. I'd played countless hours of Dwarf Fortress over the years and I couldn't see anything this game provided that DF didn't already have.Never have I been so wrong.There's a lot of goodness in the way the game plays out. The interactions between your colonists or ""pawns"" as they are often referred to is deep and interesting. Like many other games, you collect resources and build with them but the similarity ends there. There's also a rich faction model and a moderately well-designed combat system. You can expect your colony to be visited by traders, raiders, orbital trade vessels, and even survivors crash-landing in escape pods who need your help to survive their injuries.The modding community is going strong, even though the game is still in early access. There's medieval mods which turn it from a pure sci-fi game (though the sci-fi is admittedly weak on laser beams and high-tech staples) to a deranged Renaissance fair gone horribly wrong. There's even a mod which puts you square in the middle of a zombie apocalypse, as if dealing with raiders, toxic fallout, and the occasional volcanic winter wasn't enough. Sounds too hard? You control the threat level by picking a ""storyteller"", which is a great new thing I have not seen in any game before. The difficulty level also can be changed from where it launches exploding antelopes during a solar flare that destroyed your electronics down to where free food reigns down from space in cargo pods.The game has a lot of replayability already, new mods are being added every day, and the game is STILL in early access. I'm very keen on getting my money's worth out of video games, and with the wealth of choices available today there's no reason the discerning purchaser shouldn't be. However this is one of those gems you will play a lot, particularly if you're a fan of building and colony sims ... or a Dwarf Fortress fanatic like me."
