,Recommended,294100,25087088,"Posted: 23 August, 2016",all,Iridium,"Marty Villegas only wanted peace and solitude when he landed on that strange distant world, with only a handful of pre-prepared meals, a truckload of silver and his trusty dog Kiko. He quickly set to work building his mountain fortress, since he knew the galaxy was a rough and tumble place. Marty wasn't a violent man, so he set out to arrange things such that he wouldn't ever have to fire his blaster rifle in anger.It looked like his preparations were coming along well when one fateful day, a man fell from the sky in his escape pod. Marty thought for a moment about leaving the young man to his fate, but something made him venture out into the jungle, bring him back, and tenderly heal his wounds with what little medical supplies he had. Maybe it was a perspective built on the over two millenia of human history he had seen pass by in his fifty-odd biological years. Maybe it was simple human kindness. Whatever it was, he did his best to heal the stranger. The man was built like an ox, and with the bandages applied and antibiotics taken, he looked to be improving in just a few short hours. With that done, Marty set back to work on his power systems.It wasn't long after that when the battery short-circuited. A fire started in the electrical room as he was working in it, lighting Marty ablaze. He quickly ran back to the storage room to catch his senses and pat out the embers. But he knew he would have to go back, or the whole compound would burn up, leaving him with nothing and quite possibly killing his poor unfortunate guest. So Marty charged back in, and right then, the second battery exploded.Marty ran into the main hall, where the makeshift medical bed had been set up, and ran about in front of his bedridden charge, floundering here and there desperately trying to put out the flames. But it was no use. Marty collapsed on the floor, his flesh searing with fire and battery acid. Without aid, Marty would soon perish.And it was in that moment, my friends, that Marty's earlier kindness proved totally and completely in vain, because just then, the little puke got up from the bed, calmly walked around the burning form of the man who had saved his life, and left out the front door, without so much as a glance over his shoulder. Marty finally died just as the door swung closed. We will never know what horrible fate awaited Kiko in that dark Jungle.If the above sounds like the sort of scenario you would enjoy getting irrationally angry about at 1:00 AM on a Tuesday morning, then RimWorld is definitely for you. Also permadeath mode."
