,Recommended,294100,25345944,"Posted: 4 September, 2016",all,Skel1,"The trailers and screenshots of this game do not fully do it justice. What follows after the review is my experience with my first full game.The game is played very similarly to games like ""prison architect"" where the majority of your time is spent building infrastructure and economy with only minimal control over your autonomous denizens, only it adds multiple layers on top of the formula. The game is part base builder, part ""sim city"", part ""the sims"", and part ""factorio"" to compare to other games. Failing at any aspect of this game (villager happiness, resource management/logistics/crafting, combat, infrastructure) will end in the death of your settlement. Life holds on by such a thin thread that you might even say it's part roguelite.Add on top the concept of a ""digital AI storyteller"". Instead of the game throwing random disasters at your efforts, you choose a type of story teller that will progress your story with various events. These events are everything from visits from other villages, space ship parts falling from the sky, wanderers who join your village, to complete disasters.My experience:My three villagers landed on the planet, and were able to quickly build a small functioning village. Despite a few easily put down raids life was good. There was potatos, rice, fresh turkies, and hobbs was a gourmet chef. One day Eryl noticed a steel wall and felt it was dangerous, thanks for the heads up Eryl! As the fledgling colony grew so did its power requirements, and the villagers ran out of steel building a powerline to the freshly constructed walk in freezer. Well, there wasn't much steel on the map, but that ominous steel wall had plenty. The villages were dressed like cowboys, high on smokeleaf joints, and had an assortment of guns and maces, what's the worst that could happen?Senthia went down to the steel wall to deconstruct a chunk VWORP VWORP, immediately exposed and enabled were three ancient war robots. First they killed Senthia, then they started making their way to the village. The bullets fired on them did no good and were no match.  As the villagers fall one by one, a pirate raid happens at the same time. The pirates rush in with torches to set the village ablaze until they see the ancient robots. The ancient robots kill one of the pirates and the rest of the pirates flee. The village is in flames, the villagers scattered on the ground. The game ends with robots destroying every chunk of the settlement chunk by chunk.This game is amazing. 10/10. Would suffer sci-fi apacolypse again."
