,Recommended,294100,31489037,Posted: 1 May,all,BubblegumCake,"Well. What can i say? Im not a famous reviewer, but you can trust me with what im about to say next. This game, Is amazing. For those who love games like Prison architect, or dwarf fortress, This is the game for you. Its a whole new level of gameplay, and throws in so many options or ways to play. When you start, you get a globe, and where your colony will be created, is up to you from there. When you land, you have to put survival first by harvesting wood, mining steel and putting up growing zones and farms. You must then designate a stockpile, and put down beds or sleeping spots. From there, the story is yours. Will you flourish, with farms as far as the eye can see, and enough colonists to populate the world? Or will you suffer, when a dry-thunderstorm or heatwave fries your people? You can only hope that whatever storyteller you chose, is feeling mercy. Anyway, i would deffinitly reccomend this game. The developer, tynan sylvester, has a few youtube videos that show the progress, however they act as very good tutorials if you are new to the game. Then again, you could just play the built in tutorial! Have fun, and survive! Peace."
