,Recommended,294100,25684366,"Posted: 24 September, 2016",all,asspizza,"I really dont know what more I can say about RimWorld other than AMAZING.Now I do not want this to become your average review explaining how the mechanics are great and all that♥♥♥♥♥♥however, what I did think was that I would tell you a story about the game and how it came to its modern stage. RimWorld started out as a game that was literally just ""A Survival Game by the Guys That Made Prison Architect"" The Game"". I played the game in beta and absolutely loved the simplicity of it. However, I wanted more of a challenge and from the looks of it so did the rest of the beta-community. We continue to play until a week after about 20-30 posts were made about how we wanted a challenge and they said ""here, have this so more complicated stuff is added"". Just like that I knew the game was heading in the right direction and dont let my hours in Steam fool you, i easily have HUNDREDS of hours on the non-steam versions (I just dont want to lose my save haha) but I would reccomend this game to anyone that likes games ranging from RUST all the way to games such as HOI4 and CIV. It does have a learning curve for example you can get in and depending on the save you can be fine and never have to worry about  athing unitl you are ready. Or you can sleep in a cave one night and get attacked by a bunch of rabid man-eating turtles while your dog goes crazy and chews off your mother's leg, so in response you kill your dog and your mother gets angry at you because you ""killed her innocent dog"".  It is the idea that you are never safe in the RimWorld and everything that can go wrong, may end up going wrong. You need to refrigerate food, hunt, and chose how people live and how simple things such as love life in their world can impact the rest of the tribe. A perfect mixture of adventure, RPG, strategy, and casual gaming. Constant updates and an amazing modding community the game is one of the best games that I have ever played and I know that I will continue to play it in the future as I still play Prison Architect today."
,Recommended,294100,26489985,"Posted: 8 November, 2016",all,The Word-Mule,"A fantastic, in-depth space western game about building a colony full of misfits and morons. The level of complexity in the social relations system between colonists is great, and I'm excited to see where the developer goes with this game whose stated mission is to create interesting stories. But what really makes this a must-purchase is: the mods! Rimworld has a fantastically powerful modding API, wielded by an active and vibrant community, which makes it really worth your purchase even if it never fully realizes its potential. Unlike other games which are screwed if abandoned by their devs, there's little in Rimworld that can't be tweaked to your liking by mods if it's never added to the vanilla game. But that game receives major feature updates with every new alpha, so there's not much reason to worry about that. Buy it!"
