76561198007428098,Recommended,294100,26209327,"Posted: 24 October, 2016",all,Blainebow,"Definitely a quirky little game.  The first 5 times i looked at the screenshots for this game I had a little trouble believing it could be engaging.  You read that right, 5 times, if not more, because it would continually show up on my recommendations list.  I would scrutinize the screenshots in complete disbelief.  Would these little larva like bobble things elicit the kind of excitement one feels for a game that keeps them coming back the way armor sets in WOW keep people paying a monthly fee?  Obviously i was skeptical.  As it is with many things in life the only real decision can be made once you have a little skin in the game.  So i bought it. Discounted.  I'm a sucker for pretty faces and getting' something for a little less than I could have a week ago.Because bullet points are basically the end-all be-all of human existence, here is my bulleted list of impressions of this game.NOTE: 27 hours of beer infused, ""to hell with my week end obligations"", playing at the time of this writing.- Limited tech tree, in the sense that it doesn't really go anywhere.  Escalation is not game depth.  Admittedly I've not fully dug deep into this tech tree, but you kind of intuit it after about hour 16.  Well it took me that long at least.  I'm a slow learner.  Still, there are neat little surprises that a lot of games fail to deliver.  Like a television?  It took me two weeks to carve a sculpture out of stone but i had a T.V. in a day or two.  What the F are they watching?  It could not have been good, as evidenced by the depression that set in pretty quickly for the prisoners i had been feeding the flesh of their fallen compatriots.  Ok, maybe no amount of T.V. was gonna keep morale up under those circumstances.- YOU CAN EAT PEOPLE!!!!! So cool.  And along those lines your peeps will get bummed out if there are too many corpses around.  Somehow this sweet and sour contrast is heartening, but also provides an interesting kind of challenge that i haven't seen in a measurable degree in other games i've played.  Your little dudes get wigged out but stuff that happens in the game.  ""Bob, I'm really sorry bandits killed you pet llama.  We'll make them eat their friends.  Promise.""  It definitely endears you to the game and draws you closer to the little, pistol carrying, sometimes drug and alcohol abusing, larva people you're managing.  Or not managing.  The AI let's you do more or less or less or more or a little less then a lot more. You can manage and prioritize where and what they do, much like the SIMs but you can't control how they feel about it.  The little ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s, regardless of what you do will sometimes just flip each other off.  BTW, bob hates ninja7.  I had nothing to do with that.  I just needed a wall built.- You can't explore other areas even though when a new game starts, a huge map is generated.  It's not clear to a new player what the relevance is of this giant game map is meant to communicate other than, ""Look.  You can go to all these cool places."" Nope.  This is, BTW the complete same level of disappointment experienced by ""No Man's Sky"" players except the reasons are completely inverted.  If you play ""No Man's Sky"" you'll know what I mean.- The great beaver attack of 2016.  ""Bob, the colony recognises your service.  You sir are a hero.  You lost your nose, and toes.  You now walk with a limp and are a bit slower on the draw then you used to be, but, we promise, when the deer run out, and the turkeys and the crops have iced over, we will eat you last.""  Yes beavers started eating all of the trees in the area.  The colony depended on the lumber from those trees.  I as the leader of the colony had to make the hard decision.  With a  heavy heart, making sure i had a recent saved game, I sent out my finest larva people, armed to the teeth, and <snuffle> ... I'm sorry, it's still very hard to talk about, we lost two.  Once engaged, their true evil was unleashed.  Belligerent, rabid, hungry for wood and human flesh.  <snuffle>, this is very difficult, neither Bob or our colony will ever be the same.In conclusion, lot's of weird stuff can go wrong in this game, and that I guess is it's big sell and real home run.  It's not an expansive game but it's deep in it's own way.  I referred to the SIMs and I think that's a really good comparison.  A little RTS on a very small scale, a little RPG and a little SIMs.  Overall for it's scope I think this is a pretty fun game.  Definitely more fun and engaging than my initial impressions of the screen shots would have led me to believe or expect.  I can only imagine this game expanding it's scope and becoming truly all encompassing.  The mechanics are solid, UI is crude but 100% what you need for this kind of management style game, and the AI nuances make it, on a small scale as engaging as a well written and heavily scripted game like Baldur's gate.  Pretty amazing for a game that relies so much on AI."
