,Recommended,294100,29046724,Posted: 5 January,all,White Zero,"This game is astonishing. The stories that are created as you struggle to survive everything the game throws at you will stay in your head for a while, from great triumphs to the (more likely) bitter defeats. There's something morbidly satisfying of watching you colony burn to the ground, swarming with raiders, as your colonists bleed out alone on the floor.  Developer is hugely active in both development and community; both through their own website and on reddit's /r/rimworld. Mods are constantly being developed that change the dynamic of your play-style.First game to make me actively weigh the pros and cons of cannibalism. You can harvest human skin and turn it into leather for cowboy hats. Favorite crafter has asthma? Take a prisoner and harvest their lungs. Sure, the prisoner will die, but your crafter can breathe easily again! Or build towards an entirely bionic colony and travel the globe murdering everything in your way. You can just capture them all and sell them into slavery instead, which is a great way to make bank. Although drug production is a rather lucrative option as well, if you're willing to deal with the occasional addicted dog that got into your cocaine stash.You can see average hours of other reviewers, and you can see the fascinating stories.The price does appear a bit steep as you're browsing around the Steam Store, but I, personally, have found it to be worth every penny. That steep price actually led me to download the free* version to make sure I wasn't being swindled by EA promises (oh StarForge, how you've betrayed me). Three hours in, I deleted it and happily bought the official version. Now I'm actually debating on picking up another copy or two to gift to Steam friends, to both further support the developer, and spread the gift of catastrophe.Get it now.*Yeah, there isn't a free version, but I think we all got that."
