,Recommended,294100,28973478,Posted: 3 January,all,Nightmare,"RimWorld is one of those games you could play every day for the rest of your life and have a completely different outcome each and every time. If you put into perspective the amount of random generation and events, then look further at the amount of details like relations between colonists, capturing enemies or even having your own colonists captured right down to their types of injuries.. you can tell a story.It's a library of books, each game a brand new cover. Will you build a ship and escape or succumb to the dangers and mishaps around you? Will the favorite character who has fantastic shooting and a friendly face get mauled by a megasloth? Nobody knows. There is no script, only a story to be written after.Aside from all of that, completely independent of it, this game supports mods. As we see from games like Garry's mod, mods can make a game immortal. Already, even before the game is done, there is a fantastic modding community adding things that we can only hope will be added by the developers.TL;DR - Imagine prison architect 3000 years in the future except it's not a prison, it's the entire world. Oh and it has about twice the features and complexity. Plus mods."
