ses would come out with legs amputated, replaced with stumps of wood, their jaws removed and often missing several organs. He would store the remains in the freezers with the food, what the hell!The thing was he became good, almost as good as Lupos so we let him be. There must have been at least 40 graves out the back of that shack by the time things went belly up. Another day another raider attack. Bloody genius who thought mortars were a good idea for base defense, almost killed us all. Lobbed a mortar shell right into the hospital where Lupos was treating patients.Weeks quickly tended to Lupos' wounds and then went to play in his shack with his latest friends. It became apparent that Lupos right leg had been maimed due to the mortar injury. You would think after performing countless amputations and peg leg attachments on his victims Weeks would be able to do this.No the idiot failed five surgeries to help poor doc, not to mention stabbing her five times in the torso and chest. What the hell is wrong with Weeks. A few days later both Lupos and Weeks contracted severe malaria. None of us knew what to do, both doctors were dying. Irony or not Weeks died roughly one Week after contracting the disease, I threw his corpse in the newly made cremater, no one wanted to bury him out back with his victims.Lupos is a tough bird, she pulled through but was still missing a leg. I thought screw it, how hard can it be and with my none existent medical skills managed to pull it off. Lupos was up and walking again. We agreed the next time a trading ship came by with some synth legs we would get one for the doc. Sadly that never happened, the boomrat plague happened. There was so many and they came so quickly. The stupid dog Silver, who was Weeks loyal pet went into a frenzy opening the main door to the base and mauling one of our crew. We had to put the poor mutt down. It was too late though, the boomrats poured in. People panicked and stabbed them causing explosions everywhere.Only I made it out of the inferno, Lupos was too slow now that she had a wooden leg. I made it offworld in the escape pod we had built. That was the end of New Havenbrook. I leave this as a record for the poor souls I left behind. I probably won’t survive to tell the tale, I got burnt pretty good and I’m bleeding out it’s only a matter of time now. I wish Lupos was here.Speedy"
