76561198021798896,Recommended,294100,26640634,"Posted: 16 November, 2016",all,cubd.,crakc.
,Recommended,294100,26510997,"Posted: 9 November, 2016",all,Cardboard Box,"Right. I'm going to get straight to the point - after only 12 hours of game time, this is one of my new favourite games. Every single aspect of this game is amazing, and in my opinion, beautifully polished for an early access game.Let's start with the positives:- Relatively easy to get the hang of after a little while playing, even the initially confusing interface becomes easy to navigate once you know the ropes.- Beautiful yet simplistic style, similar to that of Prison Architect, adds to the game's value - from the tiniest detail (such as a swaying tree) all the way to tile-by-tile fires and various weather events. All these add to the immersion.- Due to the game's sandbox style, it offers practically endless playability. The different storytellers (game ""narrators"" who shape the world events), combined with the ability to edit your own scenarios and play how YOU want to play means you will keep going back for more.- NPC and colonist interaction is the ultimate detail, and ties in to the main reason why this game is a MUST BUY. From having chit-chat all the way to full-scale relationships, be it hostile, friendly or romantic, the multiple layers of interaction and control you are given makes it feel like you are actually affecting real lives - you will find yourself immersed in these little 2D characters' stories, from their traits and strengths to their inevitable downfall.- The game runs incredibly well, and for those of you who are sceptical about buying it, do not worry. If you have a bad system, just don't fast-forward time, and don't zoom out a lot. But the game generally runs great for me no matter what I do.Negatives (eh, more like improvements):- Colonist interaction is great, but romantic relationships should go somewhere else after marriage. This may already be a feature, but if I'm not mistaken colonists cannot get pregnant. This would be a lovely feature for natural colony expansion (but again, I might be wrong).- There is tons to do in terms of environmental interaction, but some aspects could be added to in my opinion. For example, the ability to fish in water or the sea and then store/cook fish as another source of food.Other than that, I think the game is absolutely perfect, and anyone reading this who is considering it, GO FOR IT.Really great job developers."
