76561197970941878,Recommended,294100,26093804,"Posted: 17 October, 2016",all,RED,"In an age of $60 dollar games with huge over rated budgets RimWorld gently snuck under the radar. With it's simplistic graphics and concept, I expected a mindless tower defense game, but what I got would be anything but mindless. RimWorld's attention to detail and careful considerations made (and continues to make) me feel like an architect, social scientist, therapist, prison warden, match-maker, and warlord.Not since I was in the fourth grade thinking of the Legend of Zelda have I spent the quiet moments of my day thinking of creative solutions to heat waves, mental break downs, or a stampede of rhinos. But what makes this game memorable isn't the gameplay, but the stories that are made. Buy this game, learn it, and never look back."
