76561198026451162,Recommended,294100,25954603,"Posted: 9 October, 2016",all,O Tempora!,"You choose one of 3 ai storytellers at the beginning of the game. They throw everything they can at you to burn, freeze, slaughter, starve or otherwise wipe you're beloved flegling settlement off the map. Your settlers each have their own skills and foibles which flesh them out and distinguish them. This is fundamentally a game about optimally allocating time and scant resources to meet the unrelenting disasters the game throws at you, but the settler traits and events give the world a touch of life and narrative beyond the bare strategy mechanics.The game is still being developed, but is fun to to play and feels complete in it's current form."
,Recommended,294100,25974781,"Posted: 10 October, 2016",all,jon,"Alpha 16 review.Early Access is a dangerous place to buy a game. I've been burned, specifically Towns (which is sad, because I rather enjoyed it). Many devs have the issue of not balancing out features with objectives (in-game, or the content to be able to come up with your own). Rust gets dull quickly, with most time spent leveling up, and Townes had a breaking point that you could reach within a few hours.The developer of Rimworld, however, has done a very good job of balancing out features and things to do in a Early Access Game. Hell, I put in 50 hours of playtime last week. Almost no bugs, and nothing that is gamebreaking.Lots of animals, character traits, backstory, mystery, and events.The ""ancient engine of hate"" line about the psychic drone gave me tingles, and reminded me of S.T.A.L.K.E.R.All in all, one of the only Early Access games that is worth buying in Early Access. The developer could say that this is a completed game, and I would feel it was worth the $30 that I paid. The developer, last I heard, is still working hard at updates!Pretty big mod catalog and support too, but I can't be♥♥♥♥♥♥♥to actually deal with modding and keeping things up to date. As the game is still actively being updated, you don't have the mod stability you find with Skyrim or Rise of the Reds.All in all, worth the $30 I paid for it."
