,Recommended,294100,32912152,Posted: 27 June,all,LunaticS0UL,"Did you ever hear the tragedy of Moonloop the Isloated?I thought not. It's not a tale the internet would tell you.Moonloop was a community on Pathos II, so small and self contained, it could defend itself from anything, so long as it posed no physical danger. Moonloop hosted three survivors: Gerda, Satriki, and Rogesh. Gerda, the computer. So skilled and precise, she could save anyone seconds from death. The other two were pointless horrible people, a father and son escaped from the orbiting prison.Our story begins with the creation of a simple barracks. Each of our survivors built their own beds with wood harvested from the nearby woods. ''Twas a small thing, but well lit and joyful. The cat slept next to Gerda. Over the next few weeks, the team established themselves. Gerda researched advanced technology, while the other two focused on brute work, either collecting and rearranging their belongings or hunting.One day, one rainy summer day, Gerda set out to construct a new system of production to keep the community alive. She collected the silver she needed, then walked across the map to her workplace. Satriki and Rogesh left for a hunting trip. The cat seemed to have bonded with our terrible excon friend Rogesh.You see, Gerda never liked security. She saw beautification and benefits as crucial to survival. Make it pretty, she insisted, and nobody will attack it.As those ♥♥♥♥ing awful people marched on toward their hunting spot, tragedy struck the beautiful roadside community of Moonloop. A deranged leopard, driven to madness by the excon's effective hunting or, rather, extinctification, of the local wildlife, approached the small research facility built within Moonloop. Gerda looked on at her work as the omniscient god they called ""LunaticS0UL"" helped the excons hunt. The leopard approached slowly.The excons returned home hours later, tens of bodies stacked on their carrier. The two collapsed on their beds after dropping off the corpses in the processing room. ""Where is Gerda?"" they must have wondered. The answer would not wait to show itself.The following morning, Rogesh awoke early, realizing he hasn't seen the cat since returning home. He wandered about the camp, spurred on by his god. In the top of the screen, a splash of blood. He approached slowly, then faster, then faster still. Drops became puddles became a pool. In the pool laid a pile of bones.Cat bones.He turned on a dime, scanning the nearby research room for any sign of help. He found Gerda lying in a similar pool of blood, claw marks covering her weak body. She was still breathing. She still had a pulse. He picked her up and sprinted back to the barracks, dropped Gerda in a bed, and searched for a medkit. The last one was several units away, on the other side of the map. He dropped everything, waking Satriki on his way out. Satriki would watch her and keep pressure on her wounds. Rogesh sprinted to the medkit, grabbed it, and sprinted back. But, as he entered the barracks, he realized that he had forgotten a crucial detail.Satriki and Rogesh hasn't been trained in medical techniques. They could not help. They could only watch as Gerda passed on.Gerda's death, stacked with the cat's death by leopard, broke Satriki. He took out the knife he always kept on him since escaping the prison and looked at his father. With fatal precision, he killed his aging father and ran. He reached the edge of the map and stopped. What now? Satriki stayed there for a while until he could think again. Satriki couldn't do anything outside of hunt. His whole life he had been a slave to Gerda. He couldn't survive without her advanced machinery which, for some reason, only she seemed to understand. Satriki spent his last few days attempting to scrap together a refinery table in order to eat. He died of food poisoning and starvation where he stood.Ironic. Moonloop could protect its inhabitants from boredom, but nothing else. Nothing real.RimWorld is drop-dead (pun somewhat intended) amazing. It uses AI to create events (like the leopard spawning) then you create your own story by reacting to it. If Gerda hadn't been a moron and would've invested some time in a trap or two, the story would have been completely different. It's AMAZING. Buy it."
