,Recommended,294100,29241620,Posted: 13 January,all,Psycho,"Here is a story. If this doesn't convince you to buy this game, I don't know what will.Day 1.My group of 3 survivors are name Mantis, the builder, Kimeko, the doctor, and Lynn, the hunter and cook. For the first few hours of their new lives, they create a small shelter and beds. Life is great for a while until their food rations start dwindling. Lynn decides to take matters into her own hands and begins hunting the nearby herd of elk. They feast on elk steak all night long.Day 3.The frosty jaws of winter enclose their small settlement, destroying Kimeko's fantasy of creating a small garden to grow vegetables and cotton. To avoid getting dangerously cold, the 3 of them huddle up in their shack to keep warm. After 2 days of imprisonment, cabin fever begins to grip their minds. They fight constantly, their social stances on each other crumbling quickly. Their seemingly endless supply of elk is quickly dimished to a pile of gristle and hide. Unable to take the pains coursing through her stomach, Lynn braves the biting cold, venturing out with the groups only functioning firearm to try and aquire a suitable meal for herself and her companions. As she stumbles through the tundra however, the cold overtakes her, and she is later found by a pack of wolves, who devour her stiff lifeless body.Day 9.Mantis and Kimeko barely cling to life as they sit in the darkness, eating the meager scraps of whatever rodent is unfortunate enough to scurry by. But a revelation occurs to Mantis. Rats arn't the only source of meat available. Within an hour, Mantis sits alone in the cabin, and while is belly is full for now, his mind slips further and further away.Day 14.As Mantis' food finally disappears down his throat for the last time, he can't help but think, ""What next?"". His body was too malnourished to hunt or gather, his friends were gone. Mantis comes to a decision. I will not succumb. He proceeds to reach into his pocket and pull out a small knife and flat chunk of flint. He carves off strips of wood off the wall next to him and gathers them in the corner. He then scrapes the knife quickly along the flint, causing sparks to fly, into the small pile of kindling. Mantis can feel his body shutting down as the fire builds, quickly engulfing the kindling and a part of the wall, despite the cold. Mantis lies back on the smooth wooden floor and closes his eyes, waiting for death.Day 15.A group of friendly tribesmen, well worn by the years of travelling, come across a destroyed cabin along their journey. While the small wooden structure is badly damaged, fire having obviously scorched it, leaving the remaining wreckage ashen and unmoving. Inside, they find a small amount of seared elk hide, and a corpse, blackened by the flames, with a shard of metal roofing lodged through his chest. They consider the body for a moment, wondering about its story, before carrying on looting it, before finally moving on.To this day, that is my shortest game of RimWorld ever.Buy this game. Its good."
