76561198279448481,Recommended,294100,26608463,"Posted: 14 November, 2016",all,whereiselise,"When I initially saw this game I wasn't sure if it was worth the price, but after watching some youtubers (props to Northernlion) playing this game I thought I'd give it a try and I can 100% say I have gotten my money's worth and can wholly recommend this game to anyone that's interested in it. I have sunk hundreds of hours into building up my colony and, as the game is still in development, there are many new interesting features being added which just makes me want to play more.The base game is already well polished and interesting, but the choice of mods helps to add more complex interactions between colonists, more challenging dangers to face, and many other interesting features meaning that you can always enhance your gameplay if it feels stale or repetitive.The creator is also very active on Reddit, keeping players informed of changes; responding to those who have questions and he obviously cares about the quality of his product.In regards to the gameplay I'd say that those who enjoy basebuilders and strategy games will find this game most fulfilling. There are many routes a player can take, I myself prefer the basebuilding element and the protection of the said base. However, more offensive options are being added where you can attack neighbouring enemies which I am eager to try. There is also the option to work up to an end state if a player wishes to but I actually prefer to research everything and build everything to get the most out of every colony.Overall, the game for me is a strong 9.5/10 as, although I love this game and it's probably in my top 10, I find the actual ending to be unsatisying in its current state and would like something to be added to make it more appealing to me (like the option to colonise a new planet with my colonists perhaps?).TL;DR- Really good game and worth its price, but with maybe a slightly disappointing end, 9.5/10 and you should definitely play if you enjoy strategy/basebuilder games."
