om heat stroke and starvation. Soon after, Levine dies from blood loss.Day 9: By morning, Zebo also dies from blood loss, making his cat go insane. Ophelia wakes up and also goes insane, killing and eating Zebo's cat. Bret is finally able to get out of bed, and is forced to shoot and kill Ophelia when she tries to attack him. By nightfall, Bret goes insane and wanders to Whitetaker's decaying corpse and eats it. He goes back to bed.On morning of Day 10, Bret dies of blood loss.10/10 This game is amazing."
76561197990928016,Recommended,294100,24891238,"Posted: 13 August, 2016",all,Tony Chachere,"About the Game Itself:-3 Single Player ModesClassic ""Rimworld* Mode - You start with 3 crashlanded survivors and finite resources on a planet you don't know and you're tasked to build up a base and explore the planet.The Rich Explorer Mode - You start with 1 survivor and larger amount of starting resources on a planet you don't know and also tasked to build up a new colony base on the planet.Lost Tribe Mode - You Start with 5 tribesmen whose home was destroyed by the gods and now you're tasked to rebuild your tribe on a new home.- Open world- Top Down Rouge like style graphics- Some ""Real World"" logic in the game (Such as temperature plays a part on peoples moods/actions and also affects items in game depending on what item it is such as food left in high temperatures will spoil versus in colder temperatures where they are frozen and won't spoil)- PVE Aspects- Base Building- Crafting- Pet Taming- FarmingI bought this game when I was unemployed just a few days ago. Hoping that it would give me some solace as I find another job. As I paid the amount and got the game installed, I fumbled around the main menu and confused as to the different modes I could play and what they all meant, not letting it deter me I just swung into the ""classic"" Rimworld experience labeled ""The crashlanded"". Essientially in this mode you start with three survivors who crash land on a planet with a finite amount of resources to get your bases going.Now I'd have to admit it took me more than 4 resets to finally get going and understanding the controls of the game, that equals to almost 3-4 hours of gameplay of me just trying to figure out how to play this game, what the purpose of some buildings are, and how to actually arrange my base. (I don't like using walkthroughs or gameplays for new games I like to figure things out on my own.)  But after I figured it out, boy oh boy I was in it. Even though in my second attempt my colony was wiped out by one of its own inhabitants because I didn't think that when people get divorced in game, just like in real life they probably wouldn't want to continue sleeping in the same bed with one other leading to my male colonist completely murdering my entire colony because his mental state broke from sleeping next to his ex wife after they got divorced.....  I get a call the next day after experiencing such a tragic end to my colony for a job oppurtunity, I took the job. But I wish I didn'tI wish I didn't take it.I wish I was still unemployed.Rimworld has ruined me.11/10 would stay unemployed to play this game."
