76561198011890142,Recommended,294100,24655723,"Posted: 1 August, 2016",all,Winter Steel,"If you liked the base-building of ""Prison Architect"", but wanted to be a castaway survivor in a frontier planet fighting beasts, gangs of pirates and the very elements themselves, this is the game for you. They say it reminds one of Firefly, and that's not far off the mark. I've gone days with nothing troubling happening, and then suddenly your power blows, and a rabid turtle attacks and kills a wandering boomrat and now you're trying to stop a wildfire that's sweeping through your pastures, threatening your fields and you're trying desperately to get your crops in while praying for rain.An example of how things can suddenly go off-kilter. Playing as ""Winter"" Steel, we were minding our own business, with the colony struggling to hunt and get our first crops in for the season. Suddenly a pirate raid hit from the Fire Whips, but it turns out their leader is Winter's father, Jake. We fought and won, but Winter, their best hunter and doctor, was knocked unconcious during the fight. She gets taken to her room to recover, but her father is captured, and barely holds onto life for a day, before his wounds kill him. The secondary cook, as it turns out, had some experience in cannibalism, so ate most of Jake raw, made meat pies out of the rest, and fed them to Winter, while she recovered. When she was mobile again, she had not just eaten and killed her father, but now had to live down the stigma of not having a grave to bury him in.Winter went a little insane. She wandered around in the rain unconsolably for a couple days, her friends trying to keep the place together wihtout their best hunter and planter. She dropped her rifle somewhere (where a passing pirate stole it, I assume), and then stripped naked and stood in the rain in the back pastures, until she finally got back off her knees, got dressed again and began lending a hand. But she spent a lot of time in the graveyard, looking at all the pirates she had killed over the last few seasons, and her wandering made her sick with an infection. She wandered off on another hunting trip, when a rampaging man-hunting rhinocerous gored her, before being put down by the perimeter sentry guns.Once more sick and dying of an infection, her friends tried to console her, and nurse her through the sickness, but there was no medicne, and WInter was their best doctor. She mostly recovered, but as a fragile shell of herself, wandering through her days, doing what was needed, but never recovered her soul. She spent more and more time in the cemetary, and finally died of a heart attack next to her own granite sarcophogus.Here lies Winter Steel. Murdering depressed cannabilisitic warrior of the Rimworld frontier. I think she and Alison Reynolds are my two spirit animals.Play it. Make your own tale of woe and wonder. But don't fall in love with anyone. They will all die. Hard.PS - Best death yet. Eaten alive by a horde of thirty mad, manhungry capybara. Because that's how we all wanna go."
