ndly through a hostile planet. He probably got mauled by wild animals or even killed by the pirate gang he once commanded, but I dont like that ending. I imagine that he is drifting around, begging for scraps, aimless. I like to imaging that he occasionally grabs a random passerby, and just tells his story, not unlike the old sailor from Coleridge's ""Rime of the Ancient Mariner""10/10 Early access means noting this is easily one of the best games i've played and continue to play"
