76561198061721814,Recommended,294100,25000046,"Posted: 18 August, 2016",all,papagrizz,"So I went into this game with little to no expectations.  I was looking for something to kill some time when Im between netflix binges.  It looked just ok, nothing too amazing, but I never really played anything in this genre as I usually dislike sim type games.  I bought it for $30 and initally just hoped to get a few days of enjoyment out of it and never look at it ever again.HOLY♥♥♥♥♥♥BALLS MOTHER OF GOD THIS GAME IS FUN!  I've never been so involved in a game.  There are times where I want to punch my screen and throw my computer off the top of my apartment complex.  Times when literally everything is going wrong and Im powerless to do anything about it.  Then there are times where things are going amazingly well.  You focus on making sure your best pawns are kept alive and well and happy.  You're constructing awesome bases and everything just falls into place perfectly.  The ups and downs in this game are extreme and I love it.  This game is amazing.There are a few downsides, dont get me wrong.  This is still in ""alpha"" so Ive seen a few bugs here and there but nothing too major.  My biggest gripe is the absolute lack of a tutorial.  Not even quick tips or anything.  You're kind of expected to just play the game.  Luckily I read enough reviews agreeing with that, so I watched probably a good hour or so of ""intro"" and ""how to"" videos on youtube.  Incredibly helpful.  Im not sure I would have lasted 5 minutes without them, and probably would have just left the game untouched or refunded it.  Its not the most intuitive game, but once you get the hang of things, it works out.I'm not sure Ive ever played a game that is so detailed in terms of what you're able to do.  The level of micro managment available to you is incredible.The best part of the game are the situations/stories you get.  My friend and I both bought the game together and are noobs together, and the back and forth we have telling each other about funny situations is the best part of the game.  He'll be doing amazingly well (same world, same spawn, etc) while things are blowing up and Im watching the world crumble around me, or it'll be the other way around.Verdict:  Buy this game.  It's great.  I've yet to successfully ""beat the game"" through 4-5 playthroughs but I'm enjoying the living hell out of it."
