,Recommended,294100,32397416,Posted: 13 June,all,Szpw,"Rimworld has you lead around crash-landed space colonists to establish a colony on the surface of a hostile planet.  You build a base, defend from raids, gather resources and trade with neighbouring factions.  You can even send colonists on expeditions or raid the raiders themselves!  Each colonists has different strengthes and weaknesses, and it's hard not to find yourself becoming attached to them.What makes Rimworld truly enjoyable is that there's no ""endgame"" point - a variety of threats can bring even the strongest colony to it's knees.  Perhaps a harsh winter might force you to rely on animals for food, and you quickly deplete the animal populations and your colonists starve.  Perhaps you've got sandbags, traps, turrets and well trained shooters, but your killer could easily be a plague outbreak rather than raiders.  Often the biggest danger can be from your colonists themselves: when they break, anything is possible, and insanity is a constant risk.  Due to the depth of the game, there are so many ways to deal with all of these problems, and you have to play smart to survive.As of the writing of this review, Rimworld is being actively updated and recently a big patch was just released.  On top of that, the Steam Workshop has some great mods available - I highly recommend this game!"
