,Recommended,294100,33189844,Posted: 3 July,all,HalfBurntToast,"A more appropriate name for this game would have been: 'CrackWorld'.As you might have guessed, this game is very addictive and engaging. Most famously, based on the comments, is the fact that this game creates stories for your characters as you manage them. Everyone who plays will have a different story. Since most of the comments are focusing on player stories, I figured I'd write about the game itself instead.What is this game? Think about The Sims combined with Stronghold, Banished, and Minecraft. Like Banished, you start off as a group (or one person) survivor dropped into a barren map where you have to start building farms, buildings, and products to survive. Winters are brutal and random events can occur which can throw your colony into chaos. Researching lets you build more advanced technology to help yourself survive.Like in Minecraft, you're free to design your base however you want, mine for vital resources, and are given the ability to just go hog-wild with development mode ('creative mode' in minecraft) and turn it into a true sandbox experience.Like in Stronghold, building defenses is very important depending on the difficulty. Depending on your 'Storyteller' (random event generator/Dungeon Master), raids against your base can be common and the threats can range from petty to disastrous depending on how well prepared your are. So, building your 'Castle' and its defenses is essential. Further, you'll need to have well-armed fighters ready. When raids arrive, you enlist your colonists for semi-direct control. This opens a whole tactical layer to explore.And, finally, like The Sims, your colonists are their own people. They've got their own DnD-like stat sheet along with various traits that affect how they do things and how they interact with others. They'll build relationships with the other colonists over time. This can lead to friendship, marriage, or rivalries.  They all have moods and needs that have to be managed.Unlike in The Sims, that really unhappy colonist might have a psychotic break, one-hit KO a fellow colonist and start lighting him and everything else on fire (happened to me). You're also able to capture prisoners and attempt to recruit them… or commit crimes against humanity (literally). This game gives you a pretty long leash to do things how you see fit.TL;DR: If you like The Sims, Stronghold, Banished, Minecraft, or Prison Architect, you'll probably like this game."
