76561198014628604,Recommended,294100,28880440,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,RoboGerbil,"TL;DR (Too Long; Didnt Read): This game is tough. If you played oregon trail to watch your travellers die, this is the game for you!I awoke from crysosleep to the sound of claxton alarms. Our ship was coming apart and caught in a planets gravety well. Still reeling from the sickness I tried to grab some sensible things. A pistol, some med kits, and a months worth of rations. My wife was supposed to be on this ship too but before I could make another trip to look for her the blast doors closed and I was left scrambling for the escape pod I was filling with supplies.Landfall. The planet is mostly forested. Plenty of game, should things get desparate. The nav computer on my pod says I landed somewhere near the equator. A few minutes pass as I get my bearings. There are ruined structures all around my crash site. Never more than a wall or two. Luckily I know how to fabricate these falling chunks of spaceship. I should have a shelter by nightfall.Two other escape pods crash nearby. A woman and her daughter. The woman is some kind of botanist, and the daughter seems rather useless. So I put them to work. Rome wasnt built in a day afterall. The woman started tilling a rice field. I thought it was a lost cause, but she kept at it. The daughter, I just told her to gather whatever supplies she could find from the falling debris. She comes back with a beat up rifle, a combat knife, a cafeteria worth of field rations and another medkit. Nice.I finish making the shelter and crafting some makeshift beds just in time for sundown. But things get dark here in the forest. I need some dry wood for a torch. I strap some metal together in the shape of a crude axe and head out. As Im walking through the forest I hear a howling. I thought this would be the end, so soon... But I rounded a tree and there in the clearing, the clouds had parted just for a moment, a dog. A Yellow Labrador Retriever. Grieving over her human. The body was punctured by all manner of shrapnel, too bloody for me to know if she was from the same ship I was on or if she was a local. The dog seemed friendly enough though. So with a little food she followed me back to camp.The days progressed well. Day 3, a large chunk of the spaceship crashed about a hundred feet from the house. We had enough fresh metal to last a year out here. I built a storage shed out back and added a barn onto the house in hopes to raise some of these animals wandering so close to camp. The Botanist gave up on the rice field and planted a poptato field near the sandbag fort. The popatoes are already sprouting.Day 4: A woman arrived in camp today. She is a survivor from the crashed ship, I think. She says she has some medical training, but she was really hard to speak to. Not only because she spoke another language, but because she wasnt wearing pants or underwear... Just the medical scrubs shirt and hat.Our camp was raided. I dont know how long Ive been out. Things got pretty bad after the raid. We fought off the raiders. I took a bullet to the heart, but survived. Friendly fire apparently. The raiders beat me up pretty bad too. Broken leg, bruised ribs and face. The girls got pretty shaken up about it. Then some wild animal attacked the medic. Shes all scratched to hell. All I can find is a bunny corpse though. Well even if thats the case, Im going to shoot every damn critter I find once I can walk again!Hunting went well today. Three large Ibex Rams, and two Deer bucks. I set up a meat processing workshop in the unused barn. Ill have some leather pants for our medic by tomorrow. I moved the stove over to the storage shed so the girls dont have to haul the food so far every time. I also built a crude power generator. The stove now runs on electricity. The Botanist also started a corn field. The corn is growing well. She also conscripted her daughter to help. Shes a natural. Even got the rice field starting to grow. Not well, but its better than nothing. The daughter has been acting weird since the raider attack though. She seems way more helpful.HOLY CRAP! the daughter was pulling a late night last night. and she HAD A FREAKING HEART ATTACK! Im freaking out here! If a girl in her teens has a heart attack from a bit of hard work, Im SCREWED with this BULLET IN MY HEART!Everyones sick. The daughter is still comatose. I built a medical ward on the opposite side of the field. Pretty sure were going to be using it a lot. Weve gone through the entirety of the first medical kit already. I trained the dog to protect us. Im just getting too weak ever since I was shot. I need to start a plan B in case things go south in a hurry.Day 14: This is Cammy: the daughter (as Lexi is bad with names.) I found this journal under some weird thing Lexi was working on. He is in the medical shack. He and Mom are sick with Malaria. I guess they ate some uncooked food for a bit when I was comatose. Well that [Blood drenches the rest of the page][Several pages later] Everyone is dead. The dog turned on us first. Then some cryopod crashed near the base. Used all our supplies saving the person inside only so she could screw us over when she left. Then my wife was found in another crashed cryopod. We were out of medical supplies to save her from her injuries. Then some raiders came and killed the Botanist. The doctor died from her injuries from the dog. Just me and the daughter left now. No food. No medicine. Im going to harvest all the food from the field and head toward this AI who has a space ship landed near the northern ice cap."
