76561198237594236,Recommended,294100,34664831,Posted: 1 September,all,video game man person,"This game is one of the best that I have ever played. It can be a real challenge, but it is always very fun. It is a constant struggle to survive, and manage food and resources, and the game gets progressively harder as your colony gets better, so it hardly ever gets to the point where your base is overpowered and nothing is a threat any more.Even if the base game gets boring, or if you feel that it lacks in depth, Rimworld can be very easily modded, and the majority of mods out there are very well made, and fit in with the base game without unbalancing it, or feeling unnatural. The majority of Rimworld mods add or tweak small things, for example, one makes it so you can make prosthetics, rather than having to buy them from traders, and another adds a recipie for neurotramine. There are a lot of mods that tweak small things, or add things. So if there is something you dont like about the base game, or feel is unbalanced, you can easily mod it out.Each playthrough is different and memorable: you have different colonists, all with different skills, traits, and backstories; Different events such as raids or toxic fallouts, or cold snaps effect each playthrough in a different way, and make it so that every playthrough has memorable stories. You can see what I mean by scrolling through the reveiws.Don't let the fact that it is early acess put you off, as the game feels very polished, and is virtually glitch free.This is an amazing game, with amazing features, and an amazing developer. Go and buy it"
