,Recommended,294100,24465344,"Posted: 22 July, 2016",all,babybluelas,"I first played this game at a friends house, where I quickly became an addict. It's you against everything in an effort to survive challenges that vary from a blight that might wipe out your crops, to a toxic fallout which can kill off all of the animals, and leave you relying on whatever food you have stored and can manage to grow without dying from the poison yourself until it is over. Alien insect infestations, Ancient Aliens who have suddely awoken to eat your face, a random npc colony a little ways over who decides they want to take your things.... All those and more await you in this game.The game is in early access, but I'll be honest, I've paid more for games and not gotten near the amount of enjoyment as I have from this game. There is so much customization for your scenarios, as well as even AI levels, so as to adjust the difficulty. Mods are plentiful for this game, covering everything from aesthics to enemies, from types of food, to synthetic gel that you can grow and refine into resources... This game has something that I feel appeals to anyone and everyone. It has that nice sim feel of base building and management, the strategy aspect as to facing your challenges, as well as that survival aspect. Depending on your creativity, you can even do your own little roleplay in it as well between your colonists, as they tend to be fickle creatures. Some will get married, some will cheat, break up, fight... the possibilities are endless.Give it a go, you won't regret it."
