,Recommended,294100,24748618,"Posted: 6 August, 2016",all,Doallyn,"New player to RIMWORLD, its got some problems that will hold it back from being a great title.1. Moods after an incident: If you survive a big incident that invovles a significant part of your colony then you are ♥♥♥♥ed. The mood penalty for people dying is irrelevant to the fact they need to actualty survive. Its pretty much like you lost your next door neighbour and despite the fact you are people down you will now burn the colony down like some sort of spoilt idiot2. Seige attacks: So they can plant a mortar outside of the mortar attack zone and still hit the middle of your base. Clearly a bug but i struggle to think what the point is of a siege attack in this game that can just hit the middle of your base when you have zero defensive options.3.  Research is limited. Guess this is a problem with a small dev team game, like prision architect, it just lacks depth to the whole research tree and expansion of the game. Once you've established a colony and researched the base options there really isn't anything better, no advances in gun turrents?? Its just limited in its thought process here.Overally its an alright game, but with a 100mb download you wonder what you are paying for here. It lacks the depth of a big title and the research limitations is annoying me for the money when you arent paying for big graphics then you want more from the game like sim city always delivered in lasting development.Its alright though and the replay factor is IMMENSE so its worth having in the library and gets a thumbs up for that, but i feel a steam sale  £10 is a more value for money price point."
