,Recommended,294100,24398709,"Posted: 18 July, 2016",all,Beener Schnitzel,"Ive always liked Rimworld. The new updates make it better and better and dont take away from the previous experience. I have way more than 3.5 hours playing this game. I've played this game when it wasn't on steam.I like the sandbox feel to the game. Maps are relatively small though, and once you build up a massive base and get the basics down you might be dissapointed with the overall size of the map. You run out of mine-able materials quickly and you end up relying on orbital trade and traders to come by, which without a mod rarely happen anyways.This is an early access game. Its been in the works since the end of 2013. And it shows, but its also a VERY GOOD game. And I've wasted so many nights playing this game. Wasted in a good way.The random scenarios are funny sometimes. The AI is terrible. But when you get used to it its manageable. I would recommend the 30 dollar version only. The other versions seem to just be a waste of money (I have the pirate 200.00 version of alpha 13, the 30 dollar version is literally the same but you cant control the start up and how your characters look and what you start with, meaning no challenge really.)All in all, I would recommend this game 11/10another cool thing is the people developing this game ARE actively working on the game. and have been for years. They're doing a really good job and actually listen to people and address issues when they arise."
